# ============================================================================
#  _mitosis — mitosis: Builder.io's framework-agnostic component
#             compiler.  Write once → compile to React, Vue,
#             Qwik, Solid, Angular, Svelte, Stencil, Liquid, etc.
#             (Steve Sewell / Builder.io)
#
#  Source-direct extraction from
#    https://github.com/BuilderIO/mitosis/blob/main/packages/cli/src/cli.ts
#    https://github.com/BuilderIO/mitosis/blob/main/packages/cli/src/commands/{build,compile,new}.ts
#    https://github.com/infinitered/gluegun (the gluegun library
#    by Infinite Red — creators of Ignite React Native generator)
#
#  Maintained by Builder.io (Steve "steve8708" Sewell — founder).
#  13,839 GH stars.  Mitosis is a framework-agnostic UI component
#  compiler: write COMPONENTS ONCE in a JSX-superset syntax
#  (mitosis JSX, with `useStore` for state, `useState`/`useRef`/
#  `useEffect` runtime-helpers, `useTarget` for per-framework
#  branches) and compile them to React / Vue / Qwik / Solid /
#  Angular / Svelte / Stencil / Liquid / HTML / Builder.io
#  Blocks / etc.  Used by Builder.io itself for shipping their
#  component library across multiple framework integrations
#  without maintaining N copies of the same component.  Sister
#  tools: stencil (Ionic's component compiler — in corpus via
#  _stencil), lit (Google web components — in corpus via _lit),
#  webcomponents (W3C standard), tinhat (Tin Hat component
#  compiler), turbo (Vercel monorepo runner — in corpus via
#  _turbo), nx (Nrwl monorepo — in corpus via _nx), rspack (in
#  corpus via _rspack), parcel (in corpus + STOCK via _parcel).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 14th TypeScript/Node CLI library
#  — Infinite Red's **gluegun** (infinitered/gluegun).
#  TypeScript-Node ecosystem now has 14 documented CLI libraries
#  — TYING WITH RUST AND GO at the top of the cross-language
#  taxonomy in a THREE-WAY TIE at 14 each.  🎉 TypeScript-Node
#  CATCHES UP — restoring three-way parity (Rust=14, Go=14,
#  TypeScript-Node=14).
#
#  gluegun (infinitered/gluegun) is Infinite Red's "delightful
#  toolkit for building TypeScript-powered command-line apps."
#  3,140 GH stars.  Distinguishing philosophy: gluegun is a
#  TOOLBOX-PATTERN framework — instead of declaring args via
#  schema (citty/clipanion/cmd-ts) or chained-builder (commander/
#  yargs), gluegun gives each `GluegunCommand`'s `run(toolbox)`
#  handler a RICH TOOLBOX object pre-populated with HELPERS:
#    toolbox.parameters     — parsed args (parameters.options,
#                              .first, .second, .array, .string)
#    toolbox.filesystem     — file ops (read, write, dir, copy,
#                              path, exists, append, prepend)
#    toolbox.system         — shell exec, run, which, spawn
#    toolbox.http           — fetch helper
#    toolbox.template       — handlebars-based template rendering
#                              (generate scaffolds from .ejs files)
#    toolbox.print          — pretty terminal output (info, warn,
#                              error, success, table, spin spinner,
#                              colors, divider, debug)
#    toolbox.prompt         — inquirer-style interactive prompts
#                              (ask, confirm, multiSelect)
#    toolbox.patching       — string patching (replace, update,
#                              patch in files)
#    toolbox.semver         — semantic version helpers
#    toolbox.strings        — case conversion (camelCase, snakeCase,
#                              kebabCase, pascalCase, sentenceCase,
#                              etc.)
#    toolbox.meta           — CLI metadata (version, src, plugin
#                              list)
#    toolbox.packageManager — npm/yarn/pnpm wrapper (add, remove,
#                              has, install)
#  PLUGIN SYSTEM: `.plugins('./node_modules', { matching: 'mitosis-
#  *' })` discovers extension packages by NPM PACKAGE NAME PATTERN
#  at runtime — each plugin contributes its own commands + extends
#  the toolbox with additional helpers via `toolbox.foo = ...`.
#  This is the SAME PLUGIN PATTERN that powers IGNITE-CLI (Infinite
#  Red's React Native generator) and SOLIDARITY (Infinite Red's
#  project audit tool).  Used by BuilderIO/mitosis (Builder.io
#  framework-agnostic compiler — 13,839 stars), roninoss/create-
#  expo-stack (Expo+React Native scaffolder — 2,556 stars — IN
#  CORPUS via _create-expo-stack), infinitered/ignite-cli (THE
#  FLAGSHIP gluegun user — IN CORPUS via _ignite-cli/_ignite),
#  infinitered/solidarity (Infinite Red's project audit 640 stars),
#  graphprotocol/graph-tooling (The Graph Protocol's CLI 423
#  stars), goldcaddy77/warthog (GraphQL API framework 364 stars),
#  jamonholmgren/flame (Flame AI React Native upgrader 308 stars),
#  Minds/mobile-native (Minds React Native app), JakePartusch/
#  serverlessui, serversinc/docker-backup, Theryston/jsx-mail,
#  GantMan/tfjs-runway, lucas-lm/create-md, and many other
#  TypeScript CLIs that prefer Infinite Red's toolbox+plugins
#  pattern over schema-based commander/oclif frameworks.
#
